main event: A ground-radar observation was made in Elizabeth, N.J. on 35-8-52, evaluated as probable aircraft due to clutter on the ground-radar, with a length of observation lasting 3-5 minutes and involving one object.
interesting points: Radio contact was observed 3/4 mile away from the location of the sighting.
The report was transmitted to various military and intelligence departments, including CG Newark Trancondep, HQ USAF Washington D.C, and AFB Colorado Springs.
The observer was a 16-year-old individual, as reported by Captain Maguire of the Elizabeth Police Department.
The observation occurred at 0143 hours, indicating a nighttime sighting.
There was no photograph present in the report, suggesting a reliance on radar data and eyewitness testimony.
sighted object: one very bright object covered with lights proceeding northeast
witnesses: 16-year-old observer reported by Captain Maguire of the Elizabeth Police Department
